  "Sanction Details" : "A SUSPENSION FROM ASSOCIATION WITH ANY MEMBER FIRM IN ANY CAPACITY FOR TEN (10) BUSINESS DAYS; A FINE OF $7,500; AND AN ORDER TO DISGORGE COMMISSIONS RECEIVED IN CONNECTION WITH THE UNSUITABLE TRANSACTIONS AND TO PAY PARTIAL RESTITUTION TO CUSTOMER IN THE TOTAL AMOUNT OF $6,270. AFTER CONSIDERATION OF THE RESTITUTION PAYMENT BY RESPONDENT OF $10,270 TO THE CUSTOMER, THE NASD HAS DETERMINED TO GIVE THE RESPONDENT CREDIT FOR PAYING THE ENTIRE AMOUNT OF THE DISGORGEMENT ORDER AND $4,000 OF THE FINE. RESPONDENT HAS ALSO AGREED TO MAKE AN ADDITIONAL RESTITUTION PAYMENT OF $3,500 TO THE CUSTOMER, WHICH SHALL BE CREDITED IN FULL AGAINST THE REMAINDER OF THE FINE. RESPONDENT MAY NOT REASSOCIATE WITH A MEMBER FIRM OR SUBMIT AN APPLICATION SEEKING RELIEF FROM ANY STATUTORY DISQUALIFICATION AFTER THE TEN-DAY SUSPENSION UNTIL HE SUBMITS SATISFACTORY PROOF OF THE RESTITUTION PAYMENT OF $3,500 TO THE NASD. THE SUSPENSION SHALL BEGIN ON AUGUST 5, 2002 AND END ON AUGUST 16, 2002.",
